description: Rising geopolitical tensions in West Asia  has led to a surge in Indian saffron prices. In retail, the price can reach as high as Rs 4.95 lakh per kg, which is equivalent to the cost of nearly 70 grams of gold based on Friday's rate of Rs 72,633 for 10 grams.
title: Kesar selling at Rs 4.95 lakh/kg - price of nearly 70 grams of gold

description: Former India cricketer Aakash Chopra has criticized the Chennai Super Kings' decision to keep Ajinkya Rahane as an opening batsman in the Indian Premier League, citing his subpar performance and the team's 35-run loss against the Gujarat Titans. Chopra also questioned the team's batting lineup.
title: 'Why him?': Ex-player raises concerns over Rahane's role in CSK

description: Hrithik Roshan criticizes Apple's iPad Pro ad on Instagram Stories as 'sad' and 'ignorant'. Backlash includes Tim Cook's tweet and social media criticism over the ad's metaphor for today's creative dark age.
title: Hrithik Roshan calls this Apple ad 'sad' and 'ignorant'

description: S Jaishankar praised the 1998 Pokhran nuclear tests under PM Atal Bihari Vajpayee's NDA government, emphasizing their significance for national security and the subsequent anti-terror and border infrastructure efforts. In a post on X, Jaishankar further said, "The current NDA Government has built on that foundation, robustly countering terror and building our border infrastructure."
title: 'Pokhran test ensured national security': Jaishankar recalls 1998 test
PM Modi slams Aiyar's 'Pakistan has atom bomb' remark
PM Modi slams Aiyar's 'Pakistan has atom bomb' remark

description: Gautam Gambhir's return to the Kolkata Knight Riders has sparked nostalgia and heartfelt emotions among the team's fans. During a recent event, a passionate supporter expressed gratitude for Gambhir's unwavering support. His return as a mentor signifies a homecoming for both players and fans, reinforcing hopes for further glory in the IPL.
title: 'Please never leave us': KKR fan's plea to Gambhir - Watch

description: Bajaj Auto unveiled the NS400Z, the largest Pulsar in India's mid-capacity segment. With a competitive price, impressive design, and balanced performance, it caters to the market demand for affordable yet powerful motorcycles.
title: Bajaj Pulsar NS400Z review: High performance, low cost streetfighter

description: Former Australia captain Michael Clarke provided insights into the dynamics between Hardik Pandya and Rohit Sharma, highlighting their relationship amidst speculation of discord in Mumbaui Indians in their dismal Indian Premier League campaign. Clarke praised Sharma's character and leadership qualities, expressing confidence in his ability to support Pandya during challenging times.
title: 'Rohit knows how important Hardik is for Indian team'

description: Shruti Sharma's portrayal of Saima in Sanjay Leela Bhansali's Heeramandi has garnered immense praise. Her journey from television to the silver screen reflects her dedication and versatility, showcasing a remarkable evolution in her career.
title: Shruti Sharma talks about playing Saima in Heeramandi

description: Muhammad BC arrested for unruly behavior on Air India flight, harassing crew and threatening passengers. His erratic actions, including threatening to deboard mid-air, posed a risk to all onboard.
title: One held for unruly behavior in Dubai-Mangaluru Air India flight

description: In an attempt to push through Kyiv's defensive lines, Russian forces launched a massive assault in Ukraine's northeastern Kharkiv, even as the Ukrainian defence ministry agreed that "battles of varying intensity continue'.The Moscow troops utilized artillery, bombs, and armored vehicles to enter Kharkiv, while Kyiv stated that it successfully defended against  the attacks.
title: Russia's massive assault at Kharkiv frontline raises war escalation fear

description: Cricketing legends Sourav Ganguly and Matthew Hayden, former Australia opener, have weighed in on Virat Kohli's batting position for the upcoming T20 World Cup. Ganguly praised Kohli's exceptional IPL form, suggesting he's well-suited for opening for India. Hayden, however, expressed reservations about Kohli's suitability as an opener, arguing for a left-right combination.
title: T20 WC: Virat-Rohit or Rohit-Yashasvi? Hayden has a suggestion

description: Anurag Thakur's drug addiction led to a tragic incident in Palhapur village, Sitapur district. He killed his family over a dispute, then committed suicide. The police investigation continues with a forensic team and heavy police presence in the area.
title: Man kills mother, wife and 3 children, before shooting self in UP
Solar storm hits earth; might disrupt communication, power grids

description: Gujarat Titans skipper Shubman Gill has been fined 25% of his match fees for maintaining a slow over rate during their Indian Premier League 2024 match against Chennai Super Kings. The Board of Control for Cricket in India and IPL confirmed the penalty, highlighting it as the team's second offense under the IPL's Code of Conduct.
title: IPL: Shubman Gill fined Rs 24 lakh after big win against CSK

description: How can any team beat an outfit that boasted India's all-format captain, his deputy, the world's best T20I batter and a once-in-a-generation fast bowler? However, Mumbai Indians have now become the first team to be knocked out of the playoffs race, with two games of the league stage remaining. Having led the franchise for 10 years, most young players gravitate naturally towards the phlegmatic Rohit for advice.
title: IPL 2024: How Mumbai Indians fluffed their lines

description: Former Chennai Super Kings captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni demonstrated his batting prowess in the Indian Premier League, scoring three sixes in an unbeaten 11-ball 26 cameo, bringing his total of IPL sixes to 251, putting him on par with South African cricketing master AB de Villiers. Dhoni achieved this feat in 228 innings.
title: Dhoni equals ABD, third Indian to achieve big IPL record

description: Rahul Dravid, who took over in November 2021, was handed a short-term extension till the T20 World Cup in US and Caribbean in June. His two-year contract ended with the team's defeat in the final of ODI World Cup last November. TOI has learnt that Dravid is unlikely to reapply for the current job.
title: End of Dravid era? BCCI to search for new head coach

description: Ireland secured their first-ever T20I victory against Pakistan in a thrilling match at Clontarf Cricket Club Ground in Dublin. Andrew Balbirnie, along with Harry Tector and Curtis Campher, led Ireland to a five-wicket victory with just one ball to spare. The event marked an unforgettable moment in Irish cricket, as fans celebrated the victory with jubilant scenes.
title: Watch: Fans erupt in celebration as Ireland stun Pakistan

description: Yogi Adityanath emphasizes voting for a party aligned with Lord Ram's ideals for 'Baar Baar Modi Sarkar'. He criticizes opposition leaders for comments on the Ram temple and accuses them of appeasement politics towards terrorism.
title: Ram Rajya solution to all, ensure 'baar baar Modi sarkar': Yogi

description: Bet on KKR and RR making the playoffs and SRH most likely to join them, leaving CSK, LSG and DC battling it out for the fourth spot. For RCB or GT to get into the mix would need many results to go their way. No one is yet certain of making the playoffs, but two teams (MI and PBKS) are totally ruled out.
title: CSK stay in top four despite losing to GT: IPL playoff scenarios in 10 points

description: In Rewa, MP, police rescued a kidnapped six-month-old sold to a childless couple. Investigation includes a nomadic couple from Rajasthan. The case may uncover an organized gang in Maharashtra.
title: Baby abducted from MP, sold in Maharashtra for Rs 30 lakh

description: Bengaluru faced 400 tree uprootings from strong winds, affecting roads and trapping residents indoors. Lack of moisture and breathing space, old trees, incomplete census, and insufficient manpower further worsened the tree-fall situation.
title: Summer showers see hundreds of trees tumbling. But why?

description: Aam Aadmi Party and INDIA bloc campaign for elections, with Arvind Kejriwal leading post interim bail. Delhi CM joins Punjab counterpart. Gopal Rai, Saurabh Bharadwaj, Atishi support. Sunita conducts city roadshows.
title: Lok Sabha polls: Released on interim bail, hectic campaign calendar awaits Arvind Kejriwal

description: Babar Azam equalled India batting stalwart Virat Kohli's record of most fifty-plus scores in men's Twenty20 Internationals. Both Virat and Babar now have 38 fifty-plus scores in T20Is. While Virat has a hundred and 37 fifties to his name, Babar has 3 centuries and 35 half-centuries to his credit. The highly-anticipated T20 World Cup clash between India and Pakistan is scheduled for June 9.
title: Babar Azam equals Virat Kohli's big record in T20I cricket

description: GSEB announces the Gujarat Board 10th Result 2024, available on gseb.org. Students can access their scorecards following exams held from March 11 to 26. Chairman Banchha Nidhi Pani confirms the release during a press conference. Re-evaluation options are available for dissatisfied students. The procedure involves simple steps on the official website. Additionally, results can be obtained via SMS or WhatsApp. A pass percentage of 33% is required, with supplementary exams available for those who fall short.
title: GSEB 10th result 2024 out: Gujarat Board SSC results declared

description: The most powerful solar storm in more than two decades struck Earth on Friday, triggering spectacular celestial light shows in skies from Tasmania to Britain -- and threatening possible disruptions to satellites and power grids as it persists into the weekend. The first of several coronal mass ejections (CMEs) -- expulsions of plasma and magnetic fields from the Sun -- came just after 1600 GMT, according to the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA)'s Space Weather Prediction Center.
title: Unprecedented solar activity could light up US skies

description: The upcoming election in Lakhimpur Kheri is marked by controversy surrounding Ajay Mishra 'Teni' and the tragic events in Tikunia village. Mishra, a Brahmin candidate, faces opposition from SP's Utkarsh Verma and BSP's Anshay Kalra. The constituency's demographic makeup includes SCs, STs, Kurmis, Brahmins, Muslims, Sikhs, and other communities.
title: In Teni’s Kheri, farmers’ killings a closed chapter for many
US says Israel's use of weapons may have violated international law

description: The political landscape in Unnao, Uttar Pradesh undergoes a significant transformation as the influence of former BJP MLA Kuldeep Singh Sengar lingers despite his imprisonment. Sengar's journey from power to prison reflects a narrative of ambition, betrayal, and downfall, deeply impacting the residents of Unnao.
title: ‘Sinner’ Sengar in jail, BJP counts on sadhu Sakshi for a hat-trick in Unnao

description: Hyderabad's Owaisi family stronghold faces a competitive battle in the upcoming elections, with Asaduddin Owaisi striving for his fifth win amidst tough competition from BJP and Congress. Asad's relentless campaigning efforts aim to combat declining voter turnout, while BJP's significant presence in the region adds to the electoral dynamics.
title: Low turnout, not BJP, Owaisi’s biggest worry

description: Ahead of the match between Kolkata Knight Riders and Mumbai Indians at the Eden Gardens on Saturday, a video is going viral where Rohit Sharma can be seen talking to KKR assistant coach Abhishek Nayar. Nayar is also credited with playing a big role in Rohit's comeback into the Indian team after 2011 ODI World Cup snub.
title: Watch: Rohit's animated talk ahead of MI-KKR IPL clash

description: Experts caution about deepfake impact during elections, emphasizing the need for stringent policies and citizen education to combat the spread of manipulated videos and misinformation.
title: In season of deepfakes, experts tell citizens to spot the difference
